🗺 Zoo Map

Full zoo layout visualization

🛠 Technologies Used

Python

Tkinter (GUI development)

SQLite3 (Database management)

ImageTk (UI image handling)

🗃 Database Structure

The application uses SQLite for persistent data storage.

Key Data Fields
Variable Name	Data Type	Purpose
UserName	String	Identify current user
FirstName	String	User information
LastName	String	User information
Password	String	Authentication
Email	String	Confirmation & communication
PostCode	String	Offers & marketing
User_info	List of tuples	Retrieve user data
conn	sqlite3.Connection	Database connection

The database handles:

User authentication

Membership data

Booking records

Reward point tracking

🔄 Core Functional Modules

Login Function

Registration Function

Membership Function

Buy Ticket Function

Book Hotel Room Function

Each module follows structured logic and interacts with the database to validate inputs and manage transactions.

🧪 Testing Strategy

The application was tested using:

🔹 Black Box Testing

Registration validation

Login error handling

Empty field validation

Navigation flow testing

Button redirection testing

🔹 White Box Testing

SQLite database interaction

Internal function logic

External library integration

Backend validation conditions

Testing ensured:

Proper error handling

Secure authentication

Correct page navigation

Database consistency

🚀 How to Run the Project

Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/your-username/Riget-Zoo-Adventure.git

Navigate to project directory:

cd Riget-Zoo-Adventure

Run the application:

python main.py

Make sure Python 3.x is installed.

